        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>timeout_base</name>
        <qualifiedname>bt_mesh_dfu_target_status::timeout_base</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Additional response time for the Target nodes, in 10-second increments. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The extra time can be used to give the Target nodes more time to respond to messages from the Client. The actual timeout will be calculated according to the following formula:</para>
<para><verbatim>*  timeout = 20 seconds + (10 seconds * timeout_base) + (100 ms * TTL)
*  </verbatim></para>
<para>If a Target node fails to respond to a message from the Client within the configured transfer timeout, the Target node is dropped. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
